ClipScribe Alembic migrations.

Run one backend from backend/:

    uv run alembic upgrade head

The Alembic environment resolves the active database URL through
src.db.engine.resolve_database_url(), so migrations target the SQLite or
PostgreSQL database selected by CLIPSCRIBE_DB_BACKEND.

From the repository root, `make migrate` applies SQLite migrations always and
then attempts PostgreSQL using repo-root `.env` values, skipping PostgreSQL when
it is unavailable or POSTGRESQL_URL is unset.

Use `upgrade head` to apply existing migrations. Use `revision --autogenerate`
only when authoring a new migration after updating `backend/src/db/schema.py`;
review the generated file before committing it. Production deploys should run a
separate release migration job before starting API or worker processes.
